article.headline: W. Illinois 95, Greenville 48
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Terell Parks scored 22 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Western Illinois over Division III Greenville 95-48 Wednesday night, extending their winning streak to 10 games. Parks was 11 of 11 from the field in reaching his double-double performance for the Leathernecks (13-3). Michael Ochereobia had 18 points, Jordan Foster had 14 and Don McAvoy III had 11. Ceola Clark III had six points and 12 assists. Western Illinois never trailed and led 48-20 at halftime. The Leathernecks shot 59 percent from the field, while the Panthers shot 37.3 percent. MarQuel Jones led the Panthers (7-6) with 15 points. Anthony Metzler had five rebounds. Western Illinois is 8-0 at home this season. The Leathernecks return to Summit League play when they visit Omaha on Saturday.
